Prim’s Algorithm is a classic greedy algorithm used to find the Minimum Spanning Tree (MST) of a connected, weighted, and undirected graph.

In simple terms, it starts from a single vertex and progressively grows the spanning tree by choosing the cheapest possible edge that connects
a vertex inside the tree to a vertex outside the tree, ensuring no cycles are formed.
